<subSubSection id="C31C650019B0FF776A8BA30373BBFC45" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB9368B19B0FF776A8BA30371E5FCEA" blockId="144.[189,457,868,894]" box="[189,457,868,894]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">
<heading id="D0F181E719B0FF776A8BA30371E5FCEA" bold="true" box="[189,457,868,894]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B972EA9919B0FF776A8BA30371E5FCEA" bold="true" box="[189,457,868,894]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B19B0FF776A8BA3F473BBFC45" blockId="144.[189,1398,915,978]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D0819B0FF776B0EA3F4729EFC3A" authority="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin, 2018" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[312,690,915,942]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crinita" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis id="B972EA9919B0FF776B0EA3F4729EFC3A" box="[312,690,915,942]" italics="true" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">Sphegina (Asiosphegina) crinita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24157E219B0FF77688FA3F47339FC39" box="[697,789,915,941]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but with very different genitalia. For distinguishing characters, see under 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D0819B0FF776B8FA3D07319FC46" authority="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin, 2018" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[441,821,951,978]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crinita" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis id="B972EA9919B0FF776B8FA3D07319FC46" box="[441,821,951,978]" italics="true" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">Sphegina (Asiosphegina) crinita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24157E219B0FF77690AA3D073BBFC45" box="[828,919,951,977]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31C650019B0FF776A8BA39D7216FBF3" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB9368B19B0FF776A8BA39D7168FB80" blockId="144.[189,324,1018,1044]" box="[189,324,1018,1044]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">
<heading id="D0F181E719B0FF776A8BA39D7168FB80" bold="true" box="[189,324,1018,1044]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B972EA9919B0FF776A8BA39D7168FB80" bold="true" box="[189,324,1018,1044]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B19B0FF776A8BA44E7216FBF3" blockId="144.[189,1399,1065,1127]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">
The specific epithet is from the Latin ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D0819B0FF7768A1A44E7325FBD7" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[663,777,1065,1091]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perlobata">
<emphasis id="B972EA9919B0FF7768A1A44E7325FBD7" box="[663,777,1065,1091]" italics="true" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">perlobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’, meaning ‘exceedingly lobed’ and referring to the unusually many-lobed surstylus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
